                "name": "Raiyan Kamal",
                "href": "/profile/\u09b0\u09be\u0987\u09df\u09be\u09a8-\u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2-Raiyan-Kamal"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes. It is quit possible to write Bangla using Devanagari script. Some minor adjustments will be necessary though. It'll be an interesting hobby project. But not worthwhile if your goal is to write something for the global Bangla speaking population. Bangla written in Devanagari script may not be recognized by most Bangla speaking people. The largest part of Bangla speaking people live in Bangladesh. There they experince hardly any exposure let alone formal training in Devanagari script. It's a little different in the Indian state of West Bengal. People over there are regularly exposed to the Devanagari script and many educated people there can read Devanagari script too. ",
